commit.message:
EINVAL instead of ENOTSUP for unknown flags

and make the (experimental) liblockfile2 more robust

Make L_INTERVAL experimental

Remove support for L_INTERVAL with lockfile_create(), and add a
lockfile_create2() function that always takes a struct lockargs *
pointer, and a size.

To be able to use this, compile with -DLOCKFILE_EXPERIMENTAL
or #define LOCKFILE_EXPERIMENTAL before including <lockfile.h>.
Also, link against the static library, the dynamic library
has been compiled without lockfile_create2.

dotlockfile has not been changed and '-i' works.
remove L_INTERVAL from manpage
update lockfile_touch docs
update documentation
lockfile_create: add optional struct with flag args
